  The Anambra State governor, Prof Charles Soludo, has reiterated his call to hoodlums and others causing trouble in the state to vacate their hideouts in forests and surrender their arms and accept the olive branch offered to them by his government. Soludo, in an Easter message through his media aid, Joe Anatune, said Anambra will never cede or yield their homeland to criminals According to the governor, the irrepressible spirit of the good people of Anambra State shall always triumph over the criminals in the state.